<br>
It was a quiet night in Trakanon's Teeth and the Froglok Forager was dieing about once every couple of minutes. We were luring him to the lake and then, well, kill him.  We got a few rare spawns, some nice trinkets that they decided to leave us.  About an hour or so later another group shows up.  We had just killed one of the rare spawns, Klok Denris I think, and he dropped an SK only helmet. Not that great, but since we didnt have an SK I sent a to an Iksar asking if they had any SK's, and he said no. I told him we were camping the forager, and asked if they would not pull it.  I also told him anyone in their group could loot the Sebilis Key Quest items if they like.  Also, if we get any no drop items we cant use, including the Hangman's Noose, they are welcome to loot them. He said thanks a lot, they will pull the hunter, and we had a nice little conversation.  So we continue to pull the Forager for a while. One of our members had to leave for a few minutes so we had some down time.  They pulled the forager a couple times while we medded.  We asked them nicely not to, but they just came back with things like, &quot;there is no such thing as camping,&quot; &quot;Talk to the puller, I just kill things when they get here.&quot; Well, our group got back together, adn we continued to pull continuously.  They could not keep up with us, as most were around lvl 35-40. Can anyone guess what happens next? Yep, a rare pops. Its funny, cuz as we were killing the Forager, they were watching us from not far away.  Then, when it would get low on HP's, their puller would not be there.  We noticed this, and let our puller go a little early, but I guess not early enough. Just as our puller got to the spawn, they started to pull.  Our druid got attacked by the mob, so of course he engaged it. We got it back to our spot and proceeded to kill it, quite easily and looted. Of course we got all kinds of tells saying they were going to petition us, etc.<br>
<br>
My question to the forum is, does anyone believe that killing a common mob gives you the right to the rare? I understand the &quot;Play Nice Rules&quot; that Verant has instituted. They dont really recognize the concept of camping a spawn. The thing that gets me is, we offered to let them loot anything we could not use. We told them that we were killing the Forager for his rares.  Everything seemed to be great.  We asked them to kill the Hunter, all to no avail.  Is it just me? I always thought the word &quot;camped&quot; meant something to experienced EQ players. To be honest, I am not sure of the final outcome of this, as I had to log. (The RL God spoke, and I listened.) Sorry this is kind of rambling, but I wanted to make sure I get everything in. Any feedback would be appreciated. Thanks all. <p>Tychor Westwinds<BR>
