<br>
If you go into most zones, a spawn point (not a mob) is usually considered &quot;camped&quot;. What ever spawns at that point belongs to the person/group that is camping this particular spawn point. Take for instance, L'Guk. When you camp the 3rd floor of L'Guk you usually get scribe/savant/sage/Exe/cavalier spawn points. In most cases, IMO, it would be &quot;un-kosher&quot; for a group camping the assassin room to run down and &quot;grab&quot; the savant just 'cause your group hadn't checked the spawn point yet in the past 15 seconds.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Switching gears:<br>
<br>
I would like to throw another scenario into the mix. <br>
<br>
How do all the people here feel about &quot;rare farmers&quot;?<br>
<br>
I'm not talking about the casual farmer that gets 2 or 3 of the same item, I'm talking big time &quot;rares farmer&quot;. There is a person in South Karana zone that has been farming this land for a very long time. I remember seeing this same person farming 20 levels ago. If I were to say this guy's name (50some druid), everyone would know who I was talking about that has been in South K for any amount of time. <br>
<br>
This is his scam...he farms the rares out of the zone and extorts money from people that need these items for quests, which in and of itself isn't terrible, but this guy doesn't stop. He is always in this zone, like I said before, I went through 20 levels with my main and this guy is still in the zone farming. And the kicker of it all, he is an admitted farmer. He'll tell you right now that he is a farmer! <br>
<br>
What do you all think? <br>
