<br>
As far as the common/rare spawn camping matter, this reminds me of something that happened while playing my lvl 18 rogue alt in Highpass.  I got into a gnoll group on the west end of the zone.  We were camping the gnolls, but certainly hoping that the rares would spawn and drop a PGT or CDS.  Sure, we were getting good experience, which was all I wanted, but loot is nice of course.  All of a sudden, a dwarf cleric shows up.  &quot;You guys camping the gnolls?&quot;, to which we answer yes.  &quot;You camping the named ones?&quot;, which I say we are, pointing out that they are part of the gnoll camp.  He says &quot;No, you are hunting here for experience, so you have to let me take the named ones for the loot&quot;...and things went sharply downhill from there.  He went on to say that a GM wouldn't lift a finger to help because there is no such thing as camping, and that it's not KSing if he gets the mob before we do.  When we repeated that we were camping the gnolls, he said &quot;I'll duel you for the camp&quot; which was ridiculous with him being a mid-30s character versus our highest level being lvl 20.  When his bully approach failed, he stooped lower and started grabbing every gnoll that popped.<br>
<br>
The worst part is that he stated outright that he was camping it to twink his alt or sell.  It's a sad thing, really.  People might complain, but I'm started to think that all under-30 zones (if not all zones) need to have Warrens-style looting rules applied.  It would be drastic, and there are a lot of nice items that wouldn't be available so easily via auction, but it would go a long way towards fixing this farming problem.  Odds are, it would fix the economy too, with items holding their value longer and making it a greater accomplishment to get a rare item.<br>
